			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&message.id=12327#M12327">176</a> of 332
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 333 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>What I see is a common thing coming up, is that most (For a huge change) that are in the biggest dissagreement with us, are still sticking with the main topic, "Close the gap between the top tier and mid-gear toons". The thing is, this has actually changed dramatically as the debate continues. The addition of content has been added, and the closing in gear has almost been dropped as an issue. I think Frodlin and other's have prooven over and over that casual gear that can be obtained isn't as big of a gap as some would think it is. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>We have moved on to content, which I think is the underlying reason for any of these type of discussions anyways. A desire to see something we cannot see. A longing to Progress with the people we like to play with. Like Lunrak said, we might be the minority in this issue, but I know people as well, and if this "Untapped" resourse is as big as we think it is, there is no way we could ever get them all together, cuz this "Untapped" resource is very limited to timeframe's, and the difference is sometime's very big.</DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							"One falsehood destroys a thousand truths." "Do not think of yourself higher than you ought to think" "If you are not guilty of the robbery then you should not hold on to the loot!" -NOEL BRYSON, Ph

The wise discuss ideas, the normal discuss events, the ignorant discuss other's.
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
