			>
			<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
JazzyJoyce wrote:<BR><BR>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>This is simply rediculous. Even if you had better ski gear then me, I at least have a chance to do it with crappy gear, if my skill in ski'ing is good enough. If the game was like Ski'ing, trust me, this wouldn't even be an issue of debate. Now, if it took having 72 people with you to be allowed on the ski slope, no matter how good you yourself are, then you could compare it.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ff0000>My analogy was meant for progression, not content locks... there's plenty of content out there... you have the "ski-gear" and "ski-skill" to tackle all sorts of content in single groups all the way up to MPG Trials, RS, and the Hive, and Dreadspire... it's simply not a "storyline form of progression"... something I'd be in favor of... like being able to get to a part of a weaker&nbsp;phase of the Plane of Time... or perhaps make your way into a locked "wing" of the Citadel of Anguish... smaller raids with smaller rewards... something DoN and DoD have been introducing.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ff0000></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ff0000>If you want it to be closer to what you're mentioning... you might never see the top of the most advanced slopes, because the resort only allows people who have gone through a ski-class to go on those slopes for legal issues... and the resort only offers the ski-class to groups of 50 at a time...</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Now, let's go another step and say I am a great at Organizing a raid force, and I'm known for it. HOwever, no one needs what I am doing, so they are uninterested, and therefore I end up with 24 people instead of 50 or whatever other number you want to pick. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ff0000>If you were such a great organizer, you wouldn't have a problem putting together a 54 person raid.&nbsp; Now if you can't put one together because nobody needs anything from that content... maybe it means you need to try your hand at attempting the more challenging content that people need stuff from.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>Considering you used a Velious style raid in your example, it's only pointing out how zergs are easier than a low raid count... with normal gear, Vindi can easily be single grouped... now you tell me what's easier.. getting to and killing Vindi with a single group, or organizing an entire raid to take him down.</P>
<P>Finding the number of people is half the challenge... and organization is the other half... I'm simply in support of people that can and do tackle BOTH parts of the challenge... I do support smaller raids with lesser rewards... but I'm not in favor of making them be an exact copy of the end zone content... </P>
<P>i.e. sneaking a smaller raid force into the "wing" of Anguish might have some unique nameds or some interesting storylines... but you wouldn't be taking on OMM and his buddies that a true Anguish guild is clearing...</P>
<P>or getting to fight some of the forms of lesser gods and their armies&nbsp;in the weaker phase of Time, but you wouldn't be fighting Quarm.</P>
<P>but a lot of this is moot because DoN and DoD have been pushing a lot of this type of content on us... </P>
