		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Battleblade-Xegony wrote:<BR>While there are exceptions and sporatic improvements, I think the "storyline" amd lore aspect is being overblown a bit. Guilds kill Hanvar because he's there and drops ph4t l3wts plain and simple.<BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV>That's one of the things that disappointed me... EQ used to be so open ended, people could reach 60 with high end gear without ever stepping into the same zone.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Zone levels became a bit more linear... storylines and progression were then handed out to raiding guilds... instead of a guild joining up and taking down Naggy, Vox, or dragons in Veeshan's Peak... they're now put on a path... a storyline... a form of "progression".</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Lots of people take it as, "kill Hanvar, get his ph4t l3wtz"... but there are plenty of people that want to know why Hanvar is there, what's his problem, and why you're amassing a group to kill him... those people enjoy the rewards of completing a storyline or form of progression... </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>And smaller groups are able to take on "parts" of progression... I wouldn't like to see an alternate access quest for 24 people to a top end zone like Time or Anguish... but would rather see some smaller raid force storylines that people can complete w/&nbsp;less people... rather than stop and go to another expansion because they can't amass 54 people to finish.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Again, DoN and DoD have been pushing the idea of smaller raid forces being allowed to take on complete quest lines... and hopefully we'll see more of that in the future... </DIV>
