		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<blockquote><hr>JazzyJoyce wrote:<br>I think your actually getting the main point here (finally). Looking for a clear definitive way to progress my 24 man crew through content, with a story line to make it interesting. I really think it would be a win, win situation, if Someone could go through content like this, with an alternate, yet real line of progression. Of course after getting in the zone's, the zones themselve's wouldn't be changed. If we can get into Time (The weaker phase), then to get to Quarm we would have to do the same fights any other guild did to get through the phases to reach him. If my guild is unable to do that, then at least the  member's that wish to do him, can indeed join a guild whose doing Time, and will be able to have the relevant flag's to join that guild (Those that have pre-requisits).<hr></blockquote><br><br>I see what you mean on the flags.<br><br>Additionally if there was a seperate, casual "raid" path (just like there is for endgame raiders and 6-man groups) which consisted of more than just old raid content, you could use this as a means to gear up to half-manning said older raid content.<br><br>Which IMO is a moot point anyways, because wether youre talking about 18-24 or 54-72 people, the great wall of raiding is more one of scheduling IMO.<br><br>Still, I think a seperate progression path of 18-24 player content designed for level 65-70's with low AA's and Ornate-MPG gear would be a great idea. The endgame raiders could probably single-group it, and the casual raiders/hardcore groupers could tackle it with ~2 groups. Throw some nice gear in that'd be upgrades for the casual raid/hardcore group types, and you might have a winning solution.
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
