		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>For VP key it's required a couple people do something&nbsp;in seperate area's of the zone to spawn a dragon. It's the same thing, only with more massive number's. The same strategies are used throughout the game. If I take four groups, that have to work at seperate spots of the zone, or 8 groups, it's still the same type of strategy. 10 expansions from now you will be in a guild that can do it with one group. 10 expansions from now, my guild will be able to one group quite a bit of content as well. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>BB, Did you look at my last paragraph? I am really interested in what you think of it. It's going with the route alot of folks have suggested, such as yourself, Fabled and Frodlin. Only difference would be to have a progressive route, not a homemade one. One that has a story, even if it's just to upgrade gear. Maybe a route for each type of class (Caster, Chain, plate, etc.). It would be really nice to see something like that, and would be very good for even the most casual player, as they would have a progressive route to take, with maybe some small rewards outside of gear. Kind of like doing the DoN progression up to the point where the big raids have to come in. Could send a person to MPG one day, and back to GOD the next. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Instead of going to Allakhazam and trying to make a homemade progression for each individual in the guild, we could use something like this to help us go where we should be going for our next drop of gear, or next progressive line, etc. It would be a definitive route of progression, that is backed with a storyline. "There is a creature named ___ that resides in WoS that has an item that would enhance a mighty cleric's armor. Kill this creature, and loot his _____. GO see ______ after completing this, to recieve your next set of instructions."</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>It's actually how my guild is doing it right now, we have a "homemade" progressive route for each class, some with even good/evil sides to them. However, it's homemade, and we are constantly tweakin' them as we get more information on different expansions and loot's. The whole guild get's in on it, and they are doing the raid portions twice a week.</DIV>
