		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			I'm not sure which last paragraph you are refering to, nonetheless there is a progressive route - I'm certain since I trudged though it. It has a storyline (somewhat) if you are into lore. The reason some casual plkayers don't experiance it is they get 10 feet up the road in every expansion, stop and wait for the next expansion, and then throw their hands up and say there is no road, just disconnected encounters.<br><br>IF this is what a guild experiances, of course it's useful to put together a shopping list for each class with raid targets that can be "cherry picked" for upgrades. This is not much different than what raiders experiance anyway. We do/did revisit encounters dozens of times because it has a great caster earring, aggro weapon, forcus item,...<br><br>Insted of going to Allakazam and putting together homemade progression paths, you could RAID. I suggest starting with the PoTime progression path since you like progression paths and storylines. Alternately, you could probably skip it just as some "guilds" skipped PoHate/PoFear, NToV, VT/Seru/SSra, etc. But regardless of where one enters the progression path, as you move through it EVERY class acquires useful items and an armor set that can take them to the next stage of the progression. That's how progressive content works.<br><br>Wandering about in expansions and avoiding the progression path is going to create a sence of discontinuity. That's how NOT walking the progression path works too. But CHOOSING to do this does not prevent progress either. A small guild lacking the organization to recruit others or make a guild alliance can in fact hit DoN endlessly for crystals and then obtain the items necessary to tradeskill Grandmater armor. They have a storyline too - we saw a scary cave with a sign saying "There be dragons!" and we hung around outside farming loot. Not much of a story Jazzy, but they did not enter the cave now did they.<br><br>I think that it's a little silly to claim there isn't a freeway with all those cars passing you by solely because you are seated on a tricycle. It's also a bit silly to insist because there are players on tricycles that SoE should make a seperate tricycle highway.<br><br>There is gear, a path, and adventure Jazzy. Honest.<p>Message Edited by Battleblade-Xegony on <span class=date_text>11-09-2005</span> <span class=time_text>03:12 AM</span>	
