			<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>
<HR>
Battleblade-Xegony wrote:</P>
<P>They have a storyline too - we saw a scary cave with a sign saying "There be dragons!" and we hung around outside farming loot. Not much of a story Jazzy, but they did not enter the cave now did they.</P>
<P><FONT color=#ff0000>You make it out like every raid guild is raiding simply for loot... that beating progression paths and completing objectives are pointless cause all you're interested in is ph4t lewtz.&nbsp; That obtaining access and clearing zones has absolutely no reward in and of itself.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT color=#ff0000>Take a look at the Lore Message Boards... you'll find that a lot of people at all progression levels have issues with game lore... storylines and progression paths should be viable... not limited to only those that can amass large groups... it's not like it would take anything away from those large groups that would still have their large scale raids.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT color=#ff0000>For someone so distraught over "space aliens" and&nbsp;game direction, you make it out like you'd be perfectly fine with an expansion where raiders had absolutely no lore or content, but simply large scale tasks consisting of random NPCs with no affiliation to each other.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT color=#ff0000>Some of us didn't just sit outside the caves... we amassed a smaller group and went in to take down the mighty Emoush and his three goblin mystics.&nbsp; It didn't stop you from hunting Tirranun, but it was nice to have some form of path rather than zone skipping and cherry picking mobs.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT color=#ff0000>Large forces can cherry-pick and zone-skip as well... but they also have the opportunity to follow a storyline progression... I don't see the problem with giving more of those opportunities to smaller groups.</FONT></P>
<P>I think that it's a little silly to claim there isn't a freeway with all those cars passing you by solely because you are seated on a tricycle. It's also a bit silly to insist because there are players on tricycles that SoE should make a seperate tricycle highway.</P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P><FONT color=#ff0000>Actually, lots of roads have bike paths where biking is frequent...&nbsp;and some people prefer to walk, and that's why they have sidewalks in those areas as well.&nbsp; You're suggesting that if people want to get somewhere, they should be content with running in the middle of the street (random&nbsp;encounters)&nbsp;or buy/build a car (join/build an endgame guild)... regardless if they have the means to do so.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT color=#ff0000>Jazzy seems more interested in getting on that highway to begin with... even if it means she gets run over... I just don't think it should be an alternate path to the end-game... simply an alternate path with an alternate end of progression.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT color=#ff0000>Kind of like the Seventh Hammer is today.... done with smaller groups to amass a small raid force to complete a path... </FONT>
<HR>
