<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&message.id=12347#M12347">195</a> of 332
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 203 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>How do you manage to always find the most derogatory way to put something?&nbsp; Seriously it isn't always laziness or lack of skill.&nbsp; It isn't lack of desire or any other such nonsense, it is an unjust requirement and I will try to explain yet again why.&nbsp; PoP raiding was capped at 72.&nbsp; It has been stated that by capping it they could tune it for a set number thereby keeping it a challenge, and requiring skill and strategy.&nbsp; Now where might they have gotten that number of 72?&nbsp; Did they pull it out of a hat?&nbsp; No they got that number because it was probably the average force fielded by the top 4-5 guilds on each server.&nbsp; So most of the guilds did not need to recruit to do PoP, they had the numbers already, they had steadily progressed since Kunark raiding increasing numbers over years.&nbsp; How many people were needed to do those first Naggy and Vox raids?&nbsp; Was it a more realistic number than 54?&nbsp; I think it was.&nbsp; SOE decided to tone it back to 54 after PoP, and I think largely because they knew&nbsp; 72 was just too much.&nbsp;&nbsp; Now when PoP released there were quite a few guilds that tried to get into raiding, they started recruiting to get closer to that magic number of 72.&nbsp; I know of one guild on Fennin that started at that time - they broke into Time in September of this year, that is over 2 years of recruiting and raiding.&nbsp; Their raiding started with PoP, they didn't do VT, or any of the other previous raid content, they did PoP.&nbsp; They are 1 of how many other guilds on that server that had this as a goal.&nbsp; I think it is safe to say that if it takes a guild 2 years to achieve, and only one has been able to achieve it, then the entire thing is designed to be too exclusive.&nbsp; Top 5 guilds don't have to recruit massively to do the next content, because their recruiting started 5 years ago during Kunark, they didn't need 72 or 54 at the time, they got to recruit smaller before recruiting bigger.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>This is the problem with building such a raid force today, you can't build based on kunark content because no one will join that force.&nbsp; You have to build for PoP or better, and those numbers are just too stinking high.&nbsp; Guilds that started building for PoP raiding DURING PoP are just now hitting Time and&nbsp;starting GoD&nbsp;- may I remind you that is 4 expansions later.&nbsp; Would it be right, to tell hardcore raiders for the next expansion's content they have to ramp up to 100 people in a force?&nbsp; No it wouldn't, yet it is ok to tell new guilds they have to ramp up to more than twice their size to raid content from 3 and 4 expansions ago?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>No it isn't because it has always been too hard, it is because it is technically speaking more difficult now to build a raid force than it was when the top 4-5 guilds did it.&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>And finally can anyone give a real justification to not having smaller raid content with progression and lore that virtually parallels hardcore raidcontent, with just lesser rewards?&nbsp; It doesn't seem so.&nbsp; There seem to be alot of opinions that it should be there, but no real justification, i.e. it keeps hardcore raiders from their progression, it doesn't.&nbsp; It doesn't cheapen what hardcore raiders do.&nbsp; The mid tier raiders would still be earning their rewards.&nbsp; There simply is no reason anyone has provided that a mid tier progressive path with lore shouldn't be included with each future expansion, none whatsoever.&nbsp;&nbsp; Each case opposing it seems to be that they disagree with it, basically because it is different than what they did, and therefore, according to them, would not be earning the right.&nbsp; The thing is we are talking about lesser rewards, and only SOE can determine when you have earned something.&nbsp; What a raider thinks I have and haven't earned is irrelevant.&nbsp; Just because I didn't do it the way they did doesn't mean it should have little value, or that it should remain exclusive to them.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							<img src=" http://mywebpages.comcast.net/lunrak/LunrakSOESig.gif"><br><A href= "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1125375">Lunrak of Fennin Ro</A><br><br>If you have to tell me how uber you are...then you aren't. <br>If you are uber I will already know, and wont need you to remind me.
							</div>
								
