			<DIV>Yes, I'm gonna get on the freeway with my bicycle, bassically cuz I don't have a choice. I'm in favor of what Fabled said though, an alternate route with an alternate end game. I would like to see an endgame to it though, not just "Ok, now that you have done this, you must get 51 friends to do the finale portion". If it's going to be an alternate end game, then make the end game have the same requirements used throughout the progression.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Battleblade isn't alone in his thinking, just the loudest. We have to take anything he say's into consideration as I'm sure it's not just one person's thoughts. I have to aggree with Lunrak on anyone actually having a legitimate reason as to "Why not?". </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>"can anyone give a real justification to not having smaller raid content with progression and lore that virtually parallels hardcore raidcontent, with just lesser rewards?" - I can't. I see plenty of reason to support it though.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The biggest reason that has been given as to why not, is just a counter saying "Why should we?" No matter how many reason's that are brought up, example's of non progressive route's are brought up. I think everyone that isn't in a raid guild, but of level have completed the first few steps in DoN progression that dont' require raiding, as well as other content. IF we have the proper level requirements and number's in the guild, we have started, and completed some stages of progression. IT's when the bigger number's are needed that we come short. WHat does this mean?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>It means that BB's assessment is completely unfounded, no proof whatsoever that where there is progressive content that lesser number's can do, that casual's, either wanting to be casual, or forced to be casual, have not done. I find that most have done them. Can you actually think of any content you haven't done Fabled, that your properly geared for, and can find other's in your guild to do it with, have not done? I can't really think of any I haven't completed, upon realizing it. Tipt for ikkins access. MPG trials, DoN Progression up to the first raid scenerio. Lower tier's in POP that don't need 50+ people. All the other keys that we gained along the way, ST, VP, OS, HS, etc. Most here have them, or have most of them. If they don't have them, it's ussually cuz they are amongst the better geared, levelled and AA'd in the guild, and cannot find a group or groups of people that are ready to do it with them in their same guild, but what they have done has been outside of the guild. So where is the proof that casuals don't do what they can as far as progression? </DIV>
