		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			Darknyss wrote:<br>"That obtaining access and clearing zones has absolutely no reward in and of itself."<br><br>Absolutely, obtaining access and clearing zones is rewarding - to those that do it sir, but not to those that do not. Effective effort -> reward.<br><br>"... storylines and progression paths should be viable... "<br>Oh I agree that storylines and progression paths should be as good as possible for all group and raid activities.  etc. But I disagree that 24 person content should be a seperate entity and be given special concideration to the point of being a seperate raid path.<br><br>"Actually, lots of roads have bike paths...."<br>Grouping only is perfectly viable as is small guild raiding. Frodlin's list of content doable by smaller raids was a small percentage of the available content.<br><br>"You're suggesting that if people want to get somewhere...."<br>I'm suggesting that they accept their situation in game and enjoy grouping if that's what they want, or being in a family guild if that floats their boat.<br><br>But if you want to raid, then be a tag-a-long, form a guild alliance, merge guilds, join a raiding guild, or transform your current guild into a raid guild, etc.<br><br>Don't suggest that merely because you and nine close friends were allowed to form a guild due to the ten player minimum that you are entitled to raid content, a storyline, and a progression path for ten players.<br>-------<br>Lunrak wrote:<br>"...it is an unjust requirement...."<br>No it isn't.<br><br>"So most of the guilds did not need to recruit to do PoP..."<br>Guilds recruit every expansion, particualrly at the start of expansions. And yes, I was in guilds that expanded dramatically in responce to PoP.<br><br>"I think it is safe to say that if it takes a guild 2 years to achieve, and only one has been able to achieve it, then the entire thing is designed to be too exclusive."<br>On my server at one time there were 6ish guilds in PoTime and two guilds past it. Rather than being exclusive, it's wide open and it's much easier to get there.<br><br>"...it is technically speaking more difficult now to build a raid force than it was when the top 4-5 guilds did it."<br>Cough. The server mergers re-vitalized quite a number of guilds and new ones started left and right. You are also ignoring the fact that there are a lot more players at max level now when many of us started raiding, the 85/15 rule, mudflated earlier content, content that can be skipped, and much better equipment available to those who are just starting to raid.<br><br>It's actually a LOT easier to raid now than ever before.<br><br>A genuine obstacle however is that those players most wanting and able to raid have already migrated to raiding guilds long ago. But players do retire and guilds (that want to raid) recruit more or less constantly.<br><br>What some smaller guilds are really up against is that they do not have a well established raiding culture. They are not willing to recruit, make a raid alliance, or merge to raid. Their members aren't sufficiently hardcore enough about raiding to pressure the guild to raid or they will be forced to move on. As a result you have family/friends guilds that raid less and make less progress, but that's what they and their members want sir.<br><br>There is no need for a seperate 24-person (or 10 person) raid progression path. Sufficient content already exists and it can be and has been augmented by 24-player events on THE (one and only) raid progression path.<br><br>IF your progress on that path is insufficient, then you need look no further than your effort or the effort of your guild.	
