		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>Frodlin</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>You just can't let it go...the arguement your making about justifying the gap between raider and casual is totally specious...</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>If you look at the magelo that was presented that showed the old pre-kunark warrior and gear selections raid/casual, you will indeed see the following:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Base HP: 1940</DIV>
<DIV>Gear HP Casual:294</DIV>
<DIV>Gear HP Raid: 499</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Now as you can see, the difference there was, not really all that huge.&nbsp; The base HP of the warrior was playing the LARGEST part of the stats of the class.&nbsp; Even the raid warrior was only getting about an additional 25 percent hp over his base from raid gear...</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>If you look at the difference now, a typical lvl 70 warrior will probably have a base of around 4000-4500 HP</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The casual warrior will maybe deck out to add anywhere from 4-6k hp on top of that from gear</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The top end raid warriors are adding about 10-12k on that as gear...</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>If we look at that as a reflection of the increase in base power...its not 50 percent...its just huge...too huge.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>And also, keep in mind, the difference is more than just hp...its AC, effects etc.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The difference is just too big to justify...</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>	
